<h4>COOKIES</h4>

<p>A “cookie” is a small text file sent from the Web server to a user's computer to provide information to the server on the user's accesses to that web page, and any other information that can be gathered from the system parameters that are legible by the functions in the web page. Cookies may be “temporary” (session cookies which are deleted at the end of the connection) or “permanent” (they remain on the user's hard disk, unless they are deleted by the user).</p>

<p>This website uses session cookies and persistent cookies to:</p>

<ul>

    <li><p>keep track of the surfing sessions in anonymous form;</p></li>

    <li><p>improve the site navigation;</p></li>

    <li><p>customise the services;</p></li>

    <li><p>analyse the site traffic models in aggregate form.</p></li>

</ul>

<p>The persistent cookies we use may store personal identification data exclusively if the user has registered or consented to the storage of the personal data entered on the website. Otherwise, our server only recognises that an unidentified visitor with that cookie, has returned to the website.<br>
The data is not notified or disclosed to third parties.</p>

<p>Depending on the browser, the user may disable or accept the use of cookies: in this case navigation may not be so easy and some functions of the website may not be available, or some pages may not be viewed correctly.</p>

